  "prompt": "What is a short circuit, and what is short circuiting (in simple English)?",
  "response": "A **short circuit** is when electricity finds a shorter, unintended path to travel through, usually because wires or components that shouldn't be touching each other make contact. This can cause problems like overheating, sparks, or even a fire.\n\n**Short circuiting** is the action of creating this unintended path for the electricity, often by accident, like when wires get damaged or when something conductive touches the wrong part of an electrical circuit.",
